Older women and wellbeing through the pandemic: Examining the effect of daily
online yoga lessons.

Pandya SP(1).

Author information: 
(1)Tata Institute of Social Sciences, Mumbai, Maharashtra, India.

The researcher reports the impact of online yoga lessons on a cohort of
community-dwelling older adult women in mitigating fears, anxieties and promoting
resilience, wellbeing and salutogenic wellness during the pandemic as compared to
a control group. Online yoga lessons were effective and economic class,
education, religion, marital status, and living arrangements were significant
moderators. Intervention adherence had the strongest predictor effects. The
combined effects of significant predictors were robust and latent class analyses 
indicated middle class, above threshold (>50%) lessons attendees and
self-practice doers, single, living in nonstandard families, college educated,
and Hindus, were likely to gain most.

