Context: Adolescents experience many types of gingival and periodontal diseases, 
including gingivitis, localized or generalized aggressive periodontitis, and
periodontal complications of various systemic diseases. The occurrence of
periodontal diseases is not only related to biotic factors but may also be
affected by nonbiotic factors such as oral health behaviors and practices.
