95% confidence interval [CI] 1.04-1.38), who were males (RR 1.198; 95% CI
1.01-1.29), low SOC (RR 15.93; 95% CI 13.06-19.35), and toothbrushing frequency
of less than once a day (RR 1.43; 95% CI 1.21-1.67) and children with plaque
index >1 (RR 2.765; 95% CI 2.12-3.25) presented with the higher number of
gingival units having bleeding.
