hyperreflective dots, and posterior shadowing. In all cases optical coherence
tomography angiography detected intratumoral blood vessels which were not
detectable with fluorescein angiography.
CONCLUSION: Multimodal imaging in ODM might be useful both at presentation,
increasing the diagnostic accuracy, and at follow-up, providing helpful details, 
that can help to rule out the possibility of malignant transformation and other
ocular complications.

