p < 0.05). Significant changes in general health perception showed a buffering
effect on the SDS and sense of manageability (β = - 0.406, p < 0.01, β = 0.329,
p < 0.05). As a result of the simple inclination test, SOC proved to be effective
under high levels of symptom distress; the buffering effect of sense of
