ratios (HRs) of breast cancer in relation to SoC. We identified 771 incident
cases of breast cancer during follow-up (median time: 5.2 years). No association 
was found between SoC, either as a categorical (strong vs. weak SoC, HR: 1.08,
95% CI: 0.90-1.29) or continuous (HR: 1.08; 95% CI: 1.00-1.17 per standard
deviation increase of SoC) variable, and risk of breast cancer. In summary, we
found little evidence to support an association between SoC and risk of breast
