BACKGROUND AND PURPOSE: Applying strategies that improve sense of coherence (SOC)
may positively affect adolescents' wellbeing. This may be particularly beneficial
for those with chronic conditions. Therefore, having a valid measurement tool for
SOC is important. This study assessed the validity and reliability of the Arabic 
version of the SOC questionnaire (A-SOC). Secondary objectives were to establish 
baseline data on SOC levels in a population of adolescents in the United Arab
Emirates.
METHODS: We used a cross-sectional correlational design.
