rehabilitation programme can be tolerable, reduce psychiatric symptoms, and
improve health-related quality of life for people with HD. A higher sense of
coherence seems to promote attendance rates. Further larger studies, including
the impact of cognition and disease progression on the treatment effect, are
warranted.

