Chocolate is a widely appreciated foodstuff with historical appreciation as a
food from the gods. In addition to its highly palatable taste, it is a rich
source of (poly)phenolics, which have several proposed salutogenic effects,
including neuroprotective anti-inflammatory, anti-oxidant and cardioprotective
capabilities. Despite the known benefits of this ancient foodstuff, there is a
paucity of information on the effects of chocolate in the context of chronic
