preoperative intraretinal cysts, duration of symptoms and postoperative IOP, the 
parafoveal GCL-IPL thickness in the PPV group was significantly reduced with
respect to the SB group, both at three and 12 months (F = 11.45, p = 0.001 and F 
= 12.37, p = 0.001, respectively). (4) Conclusions: In conclusion, the GCL-IPL is
reduced in thickness in eyes with macula-off RRD treated with vitrectomy and is
significantly thinner compared to eyes undergoing scleral buckling surgery.

