Aspects of Caregiving scale. We controlled for caregiver variables (e.g.,
demographics, caregiving arrangements, social support, sense of coherence) and
the neuropsychiatric symptoms of dementia. Subjective burden was higher in
primary than secondary caregivers (p = .013), but positive aspects of caregiving 
