sense of coherence and fewer symptoms of depression. Predictors for a higher
quality of life were male gender, fewer symptoms of depression, a higher sense of
coherence, higher perceived social support and living together with the marital
partner.
CONCLUSION: Family separation of Syrian refugees with a residence permit in
Germany can have an impact on their quality of life. Longitudinal studies are
needed to confirm our results and determine the long-term effects of family
separation.

