mediates the relationship between a sense of coherence and perceived professional
benefits among Chinese registered nurses. Therefore, interventions based on
social support to enhance the sense of coherence and to strengthen nurses'
perceived professional benefits should be developed.
IMPLICATIONS FOR NURSING MANAGEMENT: Nursing managers should create more learning
opportunities to improve nurses' abilities in clinical nursing and the social
support of nurses through many ways, so as to enhance nurses' sense of coherence 
and nurses' perceived professional benefits.

