Mental health problems are common among students in higher education all over the
world, so identifying those who are at higher risk would allow the targeted
provision of help. Our goal was to develop an assessment tool to identify
students at risk for vulnerable mental health status. This tool was created from 
the 12-item General Health Questionnaire and Antonovsky's abbreviated sense of
coherence scale and was tested to distinguish between those with high or low
mental resilience. Predictive ability was characterized by likelihood ratios
taking the Beck Depression Inventory and perceived health as references.
